author: The Canadian Press
title: Ed Fast says text of TPP trade deal available within days
text:
New Ed Fast says text of TPP trade deal available within days Trade minister joined outgoing Industry Minister James Moore for breakfast session at Vancouver Board of Trade The Canadian Press Posted: Oct 08, 2015 12:26 PM ET Last Updated: Oct 08, 2015 12:26 PM ET Ed Fast slams Tom Mulcair over TPP stance 3:37 Related Stories Justin Trudeau says Liberals are 'pro-trade,' offers no promises for auto 
Canada's trade minister is promising a provisional copy of the Trans-Pacific Partnership trade deal in the next few days. 
Ed Fast made the comment today at a breakfast question-and-answer session being hosted by the Vancouver Board of Trade. SPIN CYCLE: Are Conservatives the only true free traders as Harper says? 
Fast says the text is currently being translated into several languages, including Spanish. 
He also says the Canadian government has asked for the translation to be "expedited" due to the federal election. 
Fast says he believes the deal, which includes 11 other Pacific Rim countries, is worth about $3.5 billion of additional economic activity to Canada, based on estimates from his officials.
